                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d783">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">815.00/2204: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Honduras</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Belden</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tegucigalpa</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-07-11T17:00:00-05:48">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 11, 1920—5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received July 12—10:47 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>49. Serious rumors from all sections of the country and a very open
                    dissatisfaction with the present administration cause me to apprehend a
                    revolutionary movement shortly. Present Government is weak and has lost its
                    financial credit and many former friends and the general situation is very
                    serious.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Belden</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
